[{"id":"VR871934","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following most accurately illustrates where the incident ray will refract as it passes through the thin convex lens?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871934_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The thin converging lens shown in the figure has a focal length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"f\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span></span>. An object is placed a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 f\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2 f\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi></math></span></span> from the center of the lens. One incident ray, which is parallel to the principal axis, is shown on the ray diagram.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a ray and a lens with a horizontal axis through the center of the lens. Two points are on the axis to the left of the lens at distances f and 2 f, and two points are on the axis to the right of the lens at distances f and 2 f. An upward pointing arrow is at a distance 2 f to the left of the lens and an incident ray is drawn from the top of that arrow horizontally to the right to the upper part of the lens.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871934.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a ray and a lens with a horizontal axis through the center of the lens. Two points are on the axis to the left of the lens at distances f and 2 f, and two points are on the axis to the right of the lens at distances f and 2 f. An upward pointing arrow is at a distance 2 f to the left of the lens and an incident ray is drawn from the top of that arrow horizontally to the right to the upper part of the lens. The ray is deflected upward and to the right by the lens. A dashed line is drawn from a distance f to the left of the lens to the upper part of the lens. The dashed line overlaps the ray on the right side of the lens.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871934.g03.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a ray and a lens with a horizontal axis through the center of the lens. Two points are on the axis to the left of the lens at distances f and 2 f, and two points are on the axis to the right of the lens at distances f and 2 f. An upward pointing arrow is at a distance 2 f to the left of the lens and an incident ray is drawn from the top of that arrow horizontally to the right to the upper part of the lens. The ray is deflected upward and to the right by the lens. A dashed line is drawn from a distance 2 f to the left of the lens to the upper part of the lens. The dashed line overlaps the ray on the right side of the lens.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871934.g05.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a ray and a lens with a horizontal axis through the center of the lens. Two points are on the axis to the left of the lens at distances f and 2 f, and two points are on the axis to the right of the lens at distances f and 2 f. An upward pointing arrow is at a distance 2 f to the left of the lens and an incident ray is drawn from the top of that arrow horizontally to the right to the upper part of the lens. The ray is deflected downward and to the right by the lens, intersecting the horizontal axis at a distance 2 f to the right of the lens.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871934.g07.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two rays and a lens with a horizontal axis through the center of the lens. Two points are on the axis to the left of the lens at distances f and 2 f, and two points are on the axis to the right of the lens at distances f and 2 f. An upward pointing arrow is at a distance 2 f to the left of the lens and an incident ray is drawn from the top of that arrow horizontally to the right to the upper part of the lens. The ray is deflected downward and to the right by the lens, intersects the horizontal axis at a distance f to the right of the lens, and continues downward and to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871934.g09.svg\"></span></p>"],"answer":3}]